# Frontend Metadata UI (`@repo/metadata-ui`)

Declarative ERP entity surfaces. App routes wire here — do not hand-roll tables/forms for governed entities. App usage: `frontend-app.mdc`.

## Package boundaries

| Export | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| `/components` | `MetadataTable`, `MetadataForm`, section stacks |
| `/contracts` | `MetadataRenderContext`, renderer contracts |
| `/client` | Client-safe adapters and renderers |
| `/server` | Server-only resolution — apps import via feature server, not pages directly |

Metadata describes presentation; it must not own permissions, execution, or audit finality.

## Implementation rules

- Extend via **contracts + renderers/adapters** — not forked one-off JSX in apps
- Field/section/state renderers live under `src/renderers/`
- Validate inputs with package contracts; use `InvalidContractFallback` patterns
- Customization through `packages/customization` overlays — not ad-hoc props that bypass governance

## App wiring pattern

```tsx
import { MetadataSectionStack } from '@repo/metadata-ui/components'
import type { MetadataRenderContext } from '@repo/metadata-ui/contracts'

export function DocumentsView({ context }: { context: MetadataRenderContext }) {
  return <MetadataSectionStack context={context} sections={...} />
}
```

Wire feature `metadata.ts` + route view components in `apps/app` — keep domain data fetching in feature `/server`.

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ Bespoke entity table in app when metadata-ui covers the surface
<table>{rows.map(...)}</table>

// ❌ Business rules inside a renderer
if (user.role === 'admin') { /* permission finality */ }

// ✅ Metadata-driven surface + server-side permission elsewhere
<MetadataTable context={context} definition={tableDef} rows={rows} />
```

